# API Documentation Structure

This project contains documentation for the Don't Starve Together Vanilla API.

## API Directory Structure

The API documentation is organized in the `/docs/api-vanilla/` directory with the following subdirectories:

- `/components` - Documentation for game components
- `/core` - Core API functionality
- `/core-systems` - Documentation for core game systems
- `/data-types` - Lua data types used in the API
- `/entity-framework` - Entity system documentation
- `/getting-started` - Introduction and getting started guides
- `/global-objects` - Global objects available in the API
- `/node-types` - Node type documentation
- `/prefabs` - Prefab documentation
- `/recipes` - Crafting recipe documentation
- `/shared-properties` - Shared property documentation
- `/stategraphs` - State graph documentation
- `/utils` - Utility function documentation
- `/world` - World-related API documentation

## Documentation Format

All documentation files are written in Markdown with the following conventions:

- Each API element has its own dedicated page
- Code examples use syntax highlighting with ```lua code blocks
- Function signatures include parameter and return type information
- Cross-references use relative links between documentation pages

## Code Examples

Code examples should demonstrate practical usage of the API:

```lua
-- Example of component usage
local health = inst.components.health
if health ~= nil then
    health:SetMaxHealth(100)
    health:SetPercent(0.5)
end
```

## Reference Source

The documentation refers to the source code in the `dst-api` directory, which contains the actual API implementation files.

